Mauritius's Exports Expected to Increase 7% a Year, Commerce Minister Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-31T08:36:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/mauritius-s-exports-expected-to-increase-7-a-year-commerce-minister-says.html
(Corrects minister in first paragraph.)  Mauritius’s manufactured goods
exports will probably increase about 7 percent a year to reach
50 billion rupees ($1.76 million) in 2013, Commerce and Industry
Minister Showkutally Soodhun said.  Soodhun was speaking today at the annual general meeting of
the Mauritius Export Association in  Port Louis , the capital. The
Indian Ocean island nation’s exports stood at 39.8 billion
rupees in 2010, according to its statistics agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  